⍝ MatrixInverse.tc
⍝ ════════════════

      ⎕IO←1

      ⍝ Precond: B simple numeric rank≤2; square nonsingular
      ⍝ inv: ⍴Z ←→ ⌽⍴B
      ⍝ inv: ⍴⍴Z ←→ ⍴⍴B
      B ← 0.1×⎕RVAL 2 (3 3) (,0 0 1 0 0)
      B ← B+(3 3⍴3 0 0 0 3 0 0 0 3)         ⍝ ensure nonsingularity
      Z ← ⌹B
      (⍴Z) ≡ ⌽⍴B
1
      (⍴⍴Z) ≡ ⍴⍴B
1
      ⍝ inv: B+.×⌹B ≈ identity (within ⎕CT)
      ⍝ use absolute error: relative ⎕CT collapses when comparing to 0
      I ← (⍳3)∘.=⍳3
      (⌈/,|(B+.×⌹B) - I) ≤ 1E¯10
1
